# function to compute TTR
#
# @param x tokenized quanteda corpus
calculate_TTR <- function(x){
  require(quanteda)
  ntype(x)/lengths(x)
}

# load data

From scratch

## Artesanal MTLD function

# Calculate MTLD for a string
#
# @param this_snippet must be a list of strings 
# @param TTR_limit Type Token Ratio
# @param base_snippet_length num words to start calculating TTR with, default = 20
calculate_ttr_threshold <- function(this_snippet, TTR_limit = 0.72, base_snippet_length = 20) {

  current_TTR <- 1
  snip_of_snippet_length <- base_snippet_length
  
  while (current_TTR >= TTR_limit) {
    current_snip_of_snippet <- this_snippet[1:snip_of_snippet_length]
    numtypes <- length(unique(tokens(current_snip_of_snippet)))
    numtokens <- length(current_snip_of_snippet)
    
    current_TTR <- numtypes / numtokens # recalculate TTR
    snip_of_snippet_length <- snip_of_snippet_length + 1 # increment snippet_length
  }
  return(snip_of_snippet_length)
}

# Calculate MTLD for text
#
# @param text : as character
# @param TTR : TTR threshold
# @param num_snippets : num places to take TTR measurement
calculate_mtld <- function(text, TTR = 0.72, num_snippets = 25) {
  require(quanteda)
  tokenized_text <- as.character(unlist(tokens_tolower(tokens(text, remove_punct = TRUE)))) # preprocessing opts
  num_words <- length(tokenized_text)
  snippet_size <- floor(num_words / num_snippets)

  mtld_lengths <- vector()
  
  for (i in 1:num_snippets) {
    this_snippet <- tokenized_text[(i + snippet_size * (i-1)) :(snippet_size * i) ]
    
    mtld_lengths <- c(mtld_lengths, calculate_ttr_threshold(this_snippet, TTR = TTR) )
  }
  
  return(mean(mtld_lengths))
}

# Run it
art_mtld_rr81 <- calculate_mtld(rr_1981)
art_mtld_rr85 <- calculate_mtld(rr_1985)

# print
cat("MTLD Reagan-81:", art_mtld_rr81, "\n\n")
## MTLD Reagan-81: 67.04
cat("MTLD Reagan-85:", art_mtld_rr85)
## MTLD Reagan-85: 83.8

## Prepare data

# list of authors
author_list <- c("Austen, Jane", "Twain, Mark", "Joyce, James", "Dickens, Charles")

# Prepare data function
#
# @param author_name: author's name as it would appear in gutenbergr
# @param num_texts: numeric specifying number of texts to select
# @param num_lines: num_lines specifying number of sentences to sample
prepare_dt <- function(author_name, num_texts, num_lines, removePunct = TRUE){
  meta <- gutenberg_works(author == author_name) %>% slice(1:num_texts)
  meta <- meta %>% mutate(author = unlist(str_split(author, ","))[1] %>% tolower(.))
  texts <- lapply(meta$gutenberg_id, function(x) gutenberg_download(x) %>% 
                    select(text) %>% 
                    sample_n(num_lines) %>% 
                    unlist() %>% 
                    paste(., collapse = " ") %>% 
                    str_replace_all(., "^ +| +$|( ) +", "\\1"))
  texts <- lapply(texts, function(x) gsub("`|'", "", x)) # remove apostrophes
  if(removePunct) texts <- lapply(texts, function(x) gsub("[^[:alpha:]]", " ", x)) # remove all non-alpha characters
  output <- tibble(title = meta$title, author = meta$author, text = unlist(texts, recursive = FALSE)) 
}

# run function
set.seed(1984L)
texts_dt <- lapply(author_list, prepare_dt, num_texts = 4, num_lines = 500, removePunct = TRUE)

# Prepare data function
#
# @param book_id: book_id as it would appear in gutenbergr
# @param removePunct logical specifying whether to remove punctuation
prepare_dt <- function(book_id, removePunct = TRUE){
  meta <- gutenberg_works(gutenberg_id  == book_id)
  meta <- meta %>% mutate(author = unlist(str_split(author, ","))[1] %>% tolower(.))
  text <- gutenberg_download(book_id) %>% 
                    select(text) %>% 
                    filter(text!="") %>%
                    unlist() %>% 
                    paste(., collapse = " ") %>% 
                    str_replace_all(., "^ +| +$|( ) +", "\\1")
  text <- gsub("`|'", "", text) # remove apostrophes
  text <- gsub("[^[:alpha:]]", " ", text) # remove all non-alpha characters
  output <- tibble(title = meta$title, author = meta$author, text = text) 
}

# run function

# Heap's Law
# M = kT^b
# where:
# M = vocab size
# T = number of tokens
# k, b are constants

num_tokens <- sum(rowSums(joyce_twain_dfm))
M <- nfeat(joyce_twain_dfm)
k <- 44

# solve for b
b <- log(M/k)/log(num_tokens)
b
## [1] 0.4739079

# load data
data("data_corpus_ukmanifestos")

conservative_manifestos <- corpus_subset(data_corpus_ukmanifestos, Party == "Con")

# tokenize by sentences
con_sent_tokens <- unlist(tokens(conservative_manifestos, what = "sentence", include_docvars = TRUE))

# extract year metadata
yearnames <- list(unlist(names(con_sent_tokens)))
yearnames <- lapply(yearnames[[1]], function(x){strsplit(x, "_")[[1]][3]})
yearslist <- unlist(yearnames)
  
# create tibble
con_sentences_df <- tibble(text = con_sent_tokens,
                                year = yearslist)

# filter out non-sentences (only sentences that end in sentence punctuation
con_sentences_df <- con_sentences_df[grepl( ("[\\.\\?\\!]$"), con_sentences_df$text), ] 

# create quanteda corpus object
con_sent <- corpus(con_sentences_df$text)
docvars(con_sent, field = "Year") <- con_sentences_df$year

10a

# we will use a loop to bootstrap a sample of texts and subsequently calculate standard errors
iters <- 50
list_of_years <- as.list(unique(con_sentences_df$year))

#library(pbapply)
# build function to be used in bootstrapping
boot_flesch <- function(year_data){
  N <- nrow(year_data)
  bootstrap_sample <- sample_n(year_data, N, replace = TRUE)
  readability_results <- textstat_readability(bootstrap_sample$text, measure = "Flesch")
  return(mean(readability_results$Flesch))
}

# apply function to each year
boot_flesch_by_year <- lapply(list_of_years, function(x){
  sub_data <- con_sentences_df %>% filter(year == x)
  output_flesch <- lapply(1:iters, function(i) boot_flesch(sub_data))
  return(unlist(output_flesch))
})
names(boot_flesch_by_year) <- list_of_years

# compute mean and std.errors
year_means <- lapply(boot_flesch_by_year, mean) %>% unname() %>% unlist()
year_ses <- lapply(boot_flesch_by_year, sd) %>% unname() %>% unlist()

# plot results--party
plot_dt <- tibble(year = unlist(list_of_years), mean = year_means, ses = year_ses)
plot_dt <- plot_dt %>% arrange(as.numeric(year))
plot_dt <- transform(plot_dt, year = factor(year, levels = unique(year)))

# confidence intervals
interval1 <- -qnorm((1-0.9)/2)   # 90% multiplier
interval2 <- -qnorm((1-0.95)/2)  # 95% multiplier

# ggplot point estimate + variance
ggplot(plot_dt, aes(colour = year)) +
  geom_linerange(aes(x = year, 
                     ymin = mean - ses*interval1, 
                     ymax = mean + ses*interval1), 
                 lwd = 1, position = position_dodge(width = 1/2)) +
  geom_pointrange(aes(x = year, y = mean, 
                      ymin = mean - ses*interval2, 
                      ymax = mean + ses*interval2), 
                  lwd = 1/2, position = position_dodge(width = 1/2), 
                  shape = 21, fill = "WHITE") +
  theme_bw() + scale_y_continuous(breaks=seq(floor(min(plot_dt$mean)), 
                                             ceiling(max(plot_dt$mean)), by = 2)) +
  xlab("") + ylab("Mean Fleisch Score by Year") + theme(legend.position = "none")
